==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ill-favoured
<hw>Ill`-fa"voured</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Wanting beauty or attractiveness; unattractive;
deformed; ugly; ill-looking; -- usually used of a face; <as>as, an
<ex>ill-favored</ex> countenance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Ill-favored</qex> and lean-fleshed.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xli.
3.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ill`-fa"vored*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ill`-fa"vored*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ill-fed</ent>⟦br⟧
